<title>UK: Southern Elect buys 91.46 percent 'B' shares.</title>
<headline>Southern Elect buys 91.46 percent 'B' shares.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Britain's Southern Electric said on Wednesday that it had managed to buy back 45.43 million 'B' shares as part of its extended repurchase offer announced in February, 1997.</p>
<p>The group had also purchased 4.38 million 'B' share from the market. The purchases were made at 30 pence a share.</p>
<p>The company has so far bought 473.72 million shares representing 91.46 percent of 'B' shares of its capital as part of the whole repurchase scheme.</p>
<p>About 44.25 million 'B' shares remain in issue, Southern Electric said.</p>
